                  Waltho Van Claturbank, High German Doctor, Chymiſt, and Dentifricator, Native of Arabia, Deſerta, Citizen and Burgomaſter of the City of Brandipolis, Seventh Son of the Seventh Son, Unborn Doctor, of above 60 Years Experience, having ſtudied over Galen, Hypocrates, Albumazar, and Paracelſus, am now become the Aeſculapius of this Age. Having been educated at Twelve Univerſities, and travelled through Fifty two Kingdoms, and been Counſellor to the Counſellors of ſeveral Monarchs, Natural Son of the Wonder-working Chymical Doctor, Signior Haneſio, lately arrived from the fartheſt Parts of Utopia, famous throughout Aſia, Africa, Europe, and America, from the Sun's Oriental Exaltation to

his Occidental Declination: Out of meer Pitty to my own dear Self, and languiſhing Mortals, have by the earneſt Prayers and and Intreaties of ſeveral Lords, Earls, Dukes, and Honourable Perſonages, been at laſt prevail'd upon to oblige the World with this Notice;
